WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.380 --> 00:00:02.430
- Where are they now?

2
00:00:03.800 --> 00:00:04.683
- Geneva.

3
00:00:05.530 --> 00:00:08.653
One's in business, one's a doctor.

4
00:00:09.490 --> 00:00:11.270
Quite successful I think.

5
00:00:12.768 --> 00:00:15.917
- Don't they ever come here?

6
00:00:15.917 --> 00:00:18.970
- They don't know where I am.

7
00:00:18.970 --> 00:00:20.343
When I got out of prison,

8
00:00:21.500 --> 00:00:24.547
I felt if I went to them

9
00:00:25.737 --> 00:00:28.053
it could spoil their
chances in their careers.

10
00:00:29.060 --> 00:00:30.513
So I came here.

11
00:00:31.520 --> 00:00:33.370
I get news of them sometimes

12
00:00:33.370 --> 00:00:36.633
from the man who sells my
carvings in the village.

13
00:00:38.420 --> 00:00:39.253
No.

14
00:00:40.310 --> 00:00:42.863
That's the money I
earned from the carvings.

15
00:00:43.720 --> 00:00:45.653
Almost the same as what I stole.

16
00:00:47.504 --> 00:00:50.500
There were a lot of
people hurt by what I did.

17
00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:52.613
I don't even know who they were.

18
00:00:53.949 --> 00:00:55.782
So I can't repay them,

19
00:00:57.120 --> 00:00:58.880
but I would feel very much better

20
00:00:59.960 --> 00:01:02.973
if I could think of something
worthwhile to do with it.

21
00:01:06.238 --> 00:01:08.738
There, now you know my secret.

22
00:01:12.768 --> 00:01:14.543
I hope it's safe with you.

23
00:01:16.130 --> 00:01:17.647
Good.

24
00:01:17.647 --> 00:01:19.933
And now it's time you
were getting off home.

25
00:01:21.510 --> 00:01:25.053
And don't let me hear anymore
nonsense of giving in.

26
00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:28.700
You may be able to run
away from the village,

27
00:01:28.700 --> 00:01:30.753
but you can't run away from yourself.

28
00:01:31.850 --> 00:01:33.910
Go on.

29
00:01:33.910 --> 00:01:37.660
Off you go now and show
them what you're made of.

30
00:01:47.400 --> 00:01:49.800
- Teacher I must say
that the handwork this year

31
00:01:49.800 --> 00:01:51.943
is really quite exceptional.

32
00:01:55.290 --> 00:01:58.210
I'm sure that all of the
parents who are with us today

33
00:01:58.210 --> 00:02:00.493
must be delighted with this work.

34
00:02:13.850 --> 00:02:15.257
- My sister made that.

35
00:02:15.257 --> 00:02:16.090
(laughing)

36
00:02:16.090 --> 00:02:16.923
- Dani.
- Indeed.

37
00:02:18.020 --> 00:02:20.543
- I think it's best, don't you?

38
00:02:20.543 --> 00:02:25.497
- Well now that you mention
it, yes I think I do.

39
00:02:26.582 --> 00:02:29.790
- You've won the prize
Annette, you've won the prize!

40
00:02:29.790 --> 00:02:30.950
- Teacher Well having had that decision

41
00:02:30.950 --> 00:02:34.600
taken out of my hands, we
come to the boy's entries.

42
00:02:34.600 --> 00:02:37.540
Yet again the quality is so
good, but I have to confess

43
00:02:37.540 --> 00:02:40.660
there is one that stands
out above them all.

44
00:02:40.660 --> 00:02:42.730
The prize this year for the best boy

45
00:02:42.730 --> 00:02:45.467
really must go to Bernard Pile.

46
00:02:46.682 --> 00:02:49.433
(clapping)

47
00:02:49.433 --> 00:02:52.183
(peaceful music)

48
00:02:55.060 --> 00:02:57.393
(cat meows)

49
00:03:24.520 --> 00:03:26.749
- What are you playing?

50
00:03:26.749 --> 00:03:27.582
- Go away!

51
00:03:29.018 --> 00:03:31.935
(melancholy music)

52
00:03:35.184 --> 00:03:38.017
I'm playing with my fairy animals.

53
00:03:38.907 --> 00:03:42.240
But Annette said I'm not to talk to you.

54
00:03:43.478 --> 00:03:44.990
- I won't hurt you.

55
00:03:44.990 --> 00:03:47.013
And I was very sorry about your leg.

56
00:03:48.960 --> 00:03:51.637
That's why I made the animals for you.

57
00:03:51.637 --> 00:03:55.751
- You didn't make them, I
found them behind the woodpile.

58
00:03:55.751 --> 00:03:59.226
- Annette Dani, supper's ready.

59
00:03:59.226 --> 00:04:00.097
Dani!

60
00:04:00.097 --> 00:04:00.930
- Coming!

61
00:04:02.679 --> 00:04:05.429
(peaceful music)

62
00:04:13.462 --> 00:04:14.379
Come Klaus.

63
00:04:36.250 --> 00:04:37.890
- Come on, hurry up.

64
00:04:37.890 --> 00:04:39.103
- It's getting cold.

65
00:04:43.520 --> 00:04:44.353
- Annette.

66
00:04:45.300 --> 00:04:49.293
Lucien said he made my fairy
animals, but he didn't did he?

67
00:04:49.293 --> 00:04:51.540
- Dani I've told you
not to talk to Lucien.

68
00:04:51.540 --> 00:04:52.840
He'll only hurt you again.

69
00:04:53.714 --> 00:04:56.839
- Oh Annette that's not kind.

70
00:04:56.839 --> 00:04:59.777
- But I only talked to
him a teeny weeny bit,

71
00:04:59.777 --> 00:05:02.303
anyway he didn't make them did he?

72
00:05:03.813 --> 00:05:04.960
- You found them in the
woodpile didn't you?

73
00:05:04.960 --> 00:05:06.050
So how could he have done?

74
00:05:06.050 --> 00:05:07.992
Don't be so silly.

75
00:05:07.992 --> 00:05:09.737
- Well he said he did.

76
00:05:09.737 --> 00:05:13.010
But I think the fairies
made them, don't you?

77
00:05:13.010 --> 00:05:15.493
- Oh do be quiet Dani,
and eat up your soup.

78
00:05:16.470 --> 00:05:17.303
- Annette.

79
00:05:41.024 --> 00:05:42.260
- Where's Annette going?

80
00:05:42.260 --> 00:05:45.070
- I think her conscience is troubling her.

81
00:05:45.070 --> 00:05:45.903
- What's that?

82
00:05:46.787 --> 00:05:48.410
- It's a little thing inside us

83
00:05:48.410 --> 00:05:50.213
that keeps getting in the way.

84
00:05:54.330 --> 00:05:55.163
- Oh.

85
00:06:13.230 --> 00:06:15.140
- Am I to understand those little animals

86
00:06:15.140 --> 00:06:16.533
really were from Lucien?

87
00:06:19.391 --> 00:06:21.660
Oh Annette I don't know what's
going on between you two,

88
00:06:21.660 --> 00:06:23.560
but do you really think it's worth it?

89
00:06:25.564 --> 00:06:28.590
Don't you see what it's
doing to you my dear?

90
00:06:28.590 --> 00:06:30.700
You've cut of Lucien and God

91
00:06:32.260 --> 00:06:35.070
and now you're beginning to
hurt little Dani as well.

92
00:06:37.338 --> 00:06:40.255
(melancholy music)

93
00:06:45.200 --> 00:06:47.540
Think about it my dear, think very hard.

94
00:06:52.514 --> 00:06:55.514
(suspenseful music)

95
00:07:07.720 --> 00:07:10.303
(wind howling)

96
00:07:25.258 --> 00:07:27.899
(screams)

97
00:07:27.899 --> 00:07:30.066
(sobbing)

98
00:07:38.380 --> 00:07:40.547
(panting)

99
00:08:14.964 --> 00:08:16.297
Monsieur Belldo!

100
00:08:24.601 --> 00:08:25.934
Monsieur Belldo!

101
00:08:27.209 --> 00:08:29.376
(panting)

102
00:09:10.225 --> 00:09:12.975
(door knocking)

103
00:09:18.375 --> 00:09:19.708
Monsieur Belldo.

104
00:09:35.484 --> 00:09:38.151
(door rattling)

105
00:09:43.337 --> 00:09:45.504
(sobbing)

106
00:10:14.390 --> 00:10:15.223
Dear Lord.

107
00:10:17.170 --> 00:10:19.277
Dear Lord Jesus.

108
00:10:19.277 --> 00:10:21.444
(sobbing)

109
00:10:28.980 --> 00:10:30.750
Why won't you let me in?

110
00:10:32.904 --> 00:10:35.904
(melancholy music)

111
00:10:36.857 --> 00:10:39.123
Please Lord, please help me.

112
00:10:40.930 --> 00:10:42.847
Please, please help me.

113
00:10:44.929 --> 00:10:46.179
Please, please.

114
00:10:50.401 --> 00:10:53.122
(ski's scraping)

115
00:10:53.122 --> 00:10:56.205
(suspenseful music)

116
00:10:59.235 --> 00:11:00.212
Help!

117
00:11:00.212 --> 00:11:01.045
Help!

118
00:11:02.535 --> 00:11:03.368
Help!

119
00:11:04.488 --> 00:11:05.321
Over here!

120
00:11:11.894 --> 00:11:13.800
I've hurt myself.

121
00:11:13.800 --> 00:11:15.800
I can't get out of here.

122
00:11:18.523 --> 00:11:21.523
(suspenseful music)

123
00:11:27.993 --> 00:11:28.826
Oh no.

124
00:11:31.117 --> 00:11:33.117
- Can't you walk at all?

125
00:11:41.374 --> 00:11:42.815
(groans)

126
00:11:42.815 --> 00:11:44.243
Look, if you wait here

127
00:11:44.243 --> 00:11:47.430
it'd be best if I go home,
get the sledge for you.

128
00:11:48.430 --> 00:11:51.160
Don't worry, I'll be as quick as I can.

129
00:11:51.160 --> 00:11:52.160
- Won't you be cold?

130
00:11:54.851 --> 00:11:57.601
(peaceful music)

131
00:12:00.080 --> 00:12:01.240
- Lucien I won't be long.

132
00:12:02.991 --> 00:12:05.790
- Annette Voiceover Oh
why did it have to be him?

133
00:12:05.790 --> 00:12:06.623
Why?

134
00:12:08.646 --> 00:12:09.479
Why?

135
00:12:12.130 --> 00:12:12.963
Lord Jesus.

136
00:12:16.342 --> 00:12:17.243
- Dear Lord Jesus,

137
00:12:20.510 --> 00:12:23.603
thank you for sending Lucien to help me.

138
00:12:27.230 --> 00:12:30.150
I'm sorry I've been shutting
you out all these months

139
00:12:30.150 --> 00:12:34.003
'cause I wanted to hate
him, I wanted to punish him.

140
00:12:36.640 --> 00:12:37.473
I'm sorry.

141
00:12:38.376 --> 00:12:39.376
I really am.

142
00:12:43.946 --> 00:12:47.570
(suspenseful music)

143
00:12:47.570 --> 00:12:50.237
(wood cracking)

144
00:12:52.298 --> 00:12:54.898
- Annette Voiceover I
can't, please don't make me.

145
00:12:55.804 --> 00:12:56.721
Please, no.

146
00:12:58.973 --> 00:13:00.140
No no, please.

147
00:13:01.626 --> 00:13:04.626
(suspenseful music)

148
00:13:08.820 --> 00:13:10.327
- Do I have to tell him?

149
00:13:14.790 --> 00:13:15.670
- Come on.

150
00:13:15.670 --> 00:13:16.633
- No, wait.

151
00:13:18.238 --> 00:13:20.523
I want to tell you
something before we go home.

152
00:13:23.350 --> 00:13:25.900
You know that time your
horse fell off the balcony?

153
00:13:30.320 --> 00:13:31.293
Well it was me.

154
00:13:32.540 --> 00:13:33.907
I did it on purpose

155
00:13:33.907 --> 00:13:35.923
because I didn't want
you to win the prize.

156
00:13:38.890 --> 00:13:39.793
I'm sorry.

157
00:13:46.370 --> 00:13:47.203
- Come on.

158
00:13:49.760 --> 00:13:52.510
(peaceful music)

159
00:14:06.836 --> 00:14:09.919
(footsteps clicking)

160
00:14:11.210 --> 00:14:12.043
- Annette.

161
00:14:13.400 --> 00:14:15.213
Oh my dear what has happened to you?

162
00:14:16.912 --> 00:14:19.570
Your father has just this
minute gone out looking for you.

163
00:14:19.570 --> 00:14:21.170
- Yes, he's seen us.

164
00:14:21.170 --> 00:14:22.783
He's just getting some bandages.

165
00:14:26.080 --> 00:14:29.320
- Lucien, come in.

166
00:14:29.320 --> 00:14:30.573
You're very welcome.

167
00:14:32.480 --> 00:14:33.313
Come.

168
00:14:34.490 --> 00:14:35.893
Sit down both of you.

169
00:14:37.167 --> 00:14:39.273
I'll go and get you some good hot soup.

170
00:14:45.650 --> 00:14:49.800
Annette, I've tried not to interfere

171
00:14:51.580 --> 00:14:54.330
but isn't it time you forgave Lucien?

172
00:14:54.330 --> 00:14:55.657
- I have.

173
00:14:55.657 --> 00:14:57.270
- And have you told him?

174
00:14:57.270 --> 00:14:59.890
- Yes, today in the mountains.

175
00:14:59.890 --> 00:15:01.583
- And what brought this about?

176
00:15:03.169 --> 00:15:05.219
- Come on you, lets have you on the sofa.

177
00:15:10.650 --> 00:15:12.160
Gently, there we are.

178
00:15:15.656 --> 00:15:18.406
Alright, let's have a look at it.

179
00:15:23.466 --> 00:15:25.799
(groaning)

180
00:15:32.930 --> 00:15:33.950
Where Annette?

181
00:15:40.270 --> 00:15:41.103
- Ow!

182
00:15:41.960 --> 00:15:42.793
- Monsieur Burnier Is it here?

183
00:15:42.793 --> 00:15:43.626
- Yes.

184
00:15:49.360 --> 00:15:51.177
- Well, I just wanted to get out

185
00:15:51.177 --> 00:15:53.943
and think about what was
said at church last night.

186
00:15:55.220 --> 00:15:59.920
You know, about the innkeeper
not letting Mary and Joesph in

187
00:15:59.920 --> 00:16:03.533
and people who still don't let Jesus in.

188
00:16:04.667 --> 00:16:09.297
And, ow!

189
00:16:09.297 --> 00:16:10.130
Ow.

190
00:16:12.313 --> 00:16:15.290
Then I fell up by the Belldo's house

191
00:16:16.347 --> 00:16:18.110
and there was nobody there,

192
00:16:18.110 --> 00:16:21.473
but I still felt like they
weren't letting me in on purpose.

193
00:16:22.860 --> 00:16:25.210
I thought God must feel
a bit like that really.

194
00:16:26.166 --> 00:16:27.660
It was awful.

195
00:16:27.660 --> 00:16:30.210
And then Lucien arrived of all people

196
00:16:31.152 --> 00:16:33.520
and I just couldn't stand it anymore.

197
00:16:33.520 --> 00:16:36.123
And so, I had to tell him.

198
00:16:38.613 --> 00:16:40.534
- Tell him what?

199
00:16:40.534 --> 00:16:42.250
- It's a secret.

200
00:16:42.250 --> 00:16:43.083
- Oh.

201
00:16:44.121 --> 00:16:45.321
- I'll tell you one day.

202
00:16:47.314 --> 00:16:50.147
(peaceful music)

203
00:16:51.030 --> 00:16:51.980
- Come in, come in.

204
00:16:55.486 --> 00:16:58.240
Now, what can I do for you?

205
00:16:58.240 --> 00:17:01.073
(peaceful music)

206
00:17:19.867 --> 00:17:21.380
- Lucien made them.

207
00:17:24.170 --> 00:17:27.033
- These are really exceptionally good.

208
00:17:27.883 --> 00:17:29.433
They're beautiful.

209
00:17:30.410 --> 00:17:32.763
I had no idea that Lucien.

210
00:17:34.940 --> 00:17:36.990
Why did he not enter for the competition?

211
00:17:39.190 --> 00:17:40.023
- He did.

212
00:17:42.416 --> 00:17:44.393
That's what I've come to tell you about.

213
00:17:46.232 --> 00:17:48.303
He made a little wooden horse,

214
00:17:50.420 --> 00:17:53.423
but I broke it because I
was so angry about Dani.

215
00:17:55.506 --> 00:17:58.334
But I'm sorry now and I wondered
if he could have a prize

216
00:17:58.334 --> 00:18:00.133
now that you know about it.

217
00:18:01.228 --> 00:18:04.143
- But I haven't got another
prize, there were only two.

218
00:18:05.610 --> 00:18:07.923
One was given to Bernard
and the other to you.

219
00:18:10.750 --> 00:18:13.070
- Well than he ought to
have Bernard's prize,

220
00:18:13.070 --> 00:18:14.683
his were much better.

221
00:18:14.683 --> 00:18:16.573
- Oh no, we couldn't do that.

222
00:18:16.573 --> 00:18:19.403
After all, Bernard won quite fairly.

223
00:18:20.440 --> 00:18:22.193
We couldn't take his prize away.

224
00:18:26.230 --> 00:18:30.110
If you really want Lucien to have a prize

225
00:18:32.860 --> 00:18:37.483
then I think you should give him yours.

226
00:18:39.380 --> 00:18:41.853
After all it was your fault wasn't it?

227
00:18:43.576 --> 00:18:44.409
Hmm?

228
00:18:50.420 --> 00:18:54.283
It seems we have a late entry
for the handwork competition.

229
00:18:55.630 --> 00:18:59.023
Indeed, I must say I was
as surprised as you are.

230
00:19:01.090 --> 00:19:03.490
Normally I would not
consider such a late entry.

231
00:19:04.760 --> 00:19:08.210
However, during the holidays

232
00:19:08.210 --> 00:19:11.100
I came across such a
good piece of woodcarving

233
00:19:11.100 --> 00:19:14.233
that I've decided to award
another prize for it.

234
00:19:26.850 --> 00:19:31.053
Lucien, would you like to
come up and receive it?

235
00:19:36.721 --> 00:19:37.554
- Thank you.

236
00:19:37.554 --> 00:19:40.561
- Well done, you deserve it.

237
00:19:40.561 --> 00:19:41.561
- Thank you.

238
00:19:45.259 --> 00:19:47.509
- Annette it's like yours.

239
00:19:48.390 --> 00:19:49.960
- Is it?

240
00:19:49.960 --> 00:19:52.793
(peaceful music)

241
00:19:57.173 --> 00:20:01.020
I think you ought to
keep it, it's your book.

242
00:20:01.020 --> 00:20:02.440
- No, it's yours now.

243
00:20:02.440 --> 00:20:04.240
The teacher said so.

244
00:20:04.240 --> 00:20:05.340
You've got to keep it.

245
00:20:06.270 --> 00:20:07.440
- Well I tell you what,

246
00:20:07.440 --> 00:20:10.007
why don't I have it this month
and you have it the next?

247
00:20:10.007 --> 00:20:12.107
- And we'll change every month, all right.

248
00:20:12.944 --> 00:20:15.777
(peaceful music)

249
00:20:16.780 --> 00:20:19.000
Dani, what are you doing here?

250
00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:21.220
- Granny said I could come here,

251
00:20:21.220 --> 00:20:23.220
'cause dinner's ready and I've had mine.

252
00:20:24.250 --> 00:20:25.970
- You shouldn't have come so far.

253
00:20:25.970 --> 00:20:27.883
- I thought you'd be back sooner.

254
00:20:31.090 --> 00:20:32.030
- Come on.

255
00:20:32.030 --> 00:20:33.257
- Oh, my leg hurts.

256
00:20:35.020 --> 00:20:36.810
- Shall I carry him?

257
00:20:36.810 --> 00:20:37.910
- Would you like that?

258
00:20:49.716 --> 00:20:50.549
- Woo hoo!

259
00:20:51.508 --> 00:20:54.341
(peaceful music)

260
00:21:03.158 --> 00:21:05.158
- What are you thinking?

261
00:21:07.014 --> 00:21:07.847
- Dani.

262
00:21:08.849 --> 00:21:13.849
- Don't you think it's time
you put all that behind you?

263
00:21:13.875 --> 00:21:16.625
- It was going so well, and then.

264
00:21:20.896 --> 00:21:23.743
Isn't there anything we can do for him?

265
00:21:23.743 --> 00:21:25.993
- No, I don't think we can.

266
00:21:29.390 --> 00:21:31.240
- Marie Oh, I thought I'd never make it.

267
00:21:31.240 --> 00:21:33.253
- Come on, you must be frozen.

268
00:21:38.000 --> 00:21:38.833
What's this?

269
00:21:42.090 --> 00:21:43.143
- Money I think.

270
00:21:45.130 --> 00:21:46.263
- What's it for?

271
00:21:47.330 --> 00:21:48.423
- Got it as a tip.

272
00:21:50.350 --> 00:21:51.705
- Really?

273
00:21:51.705 --> 00:21:55.640
- Monsieur Givert, he's a
doctor from down by the lake.

274
00:21:55.640 --> 00:21:57.340
Quite famous I believe.

275
00:21:57.340 --> 00:21:58.763
- Isn't that nice of him?

276
00:21:59.894 --> 00:22:01.610
- Madam was telling me he's got a clinic.

277
00:22:01.610 --> 00:22:03.283
People come from all over the world,

278
00:22:03.283 --> 00:22:05.830
he's some sort of bone specialist

279
00:22:05.830 --> 00:22:07.330
Honestly he was ever so nice.

280
00:22:07.330 --> 00:22:09.515
- Can he mend broken legs?

281
00:22:09.515 --> 00:22:10.715
- I would think so, yes.

282
00:22:11.805 --> 00:22:15.037
Oh, Lucien, you're not still
thinking about Dani are you?

283
00:22:15.037 --> 00:22:17.211
- Could he do it?

284
00:22:17.211 --> 00:22:20.490
- I suppose so but have no
idea how much it would cost?

285
00:22:20.490 --> 00:22:21.323
- No.

286
00:22:22.540 --> 00:22:23.927
- Nor have I.

287
00:22:23.927 --> 00:22:26.800
But it'll be far more than
the Burniers could afford.

288
00:22:26.800 --> 00:22:28.600
- Forget about Dani, Lucien.

289
00:22:28.600 --> 00:22:29.860
It's over with.

290
00:22:29.860 --> 00:22:31.790
- But would he just come
and have a look at Dani?

291
00:22:31.790 --> 00:22:33.040
- What good will that do?

292
00:22:34.850 --> 00:22:36.430
- I just thought that we could find out

293
00:22:36.430 --> 00:22:37.823
if anything could be done.

294
00:22:42.290 --> 00:22:44.728
- He leaves tomorrow early.

295
00:22:44.728 --> 00:22:45.680
- We could go now.

296
00:22:45.680 --> 00:22:46.513
- Marie How?

297
00:22:46.513 --> 00:22:47.393
- On the train.

298
00:22:49.730 --> 00:22:51.456
- It's too late.

299
00:22:51.456 --> 00:22:54.200
- Not if we hurry.

300
00:22:54.200 --> 00:22:55.663
- Lucien don't be silly.

301
00:23:26.709 --> 00:23:29.709
(suspenseful music)

302
00:23:51.100 --> 00:23:53.683
(wind howling)

303
00:24:11.820 --> 00:24:12.653
- Who's that?

304
00:24:17.790 --> 00:24:20.073
My boy what brings you
here in this weather?

305
00:24:23.606 --> 00:24:25.856
(coughing)

306
00:24:30.292 --> 00:24:31.792
Are you all right?

307
00:24:34.052 --> 00:24:36.773
- You know you once said
you were saving your money

308
00:24:36.773 --> 00:24:39.731
to give to something worthwhile.

309
00:24:39.731 --> 00:24:40.564
- Yes.

310
00:24:41.482 --> 00:24:44.550
- Well, I think I've found
someone who really needs it.

311
00:24:44.550 --> 00:24:46.170
If you will give me your money,

312
00:24:46.170 --> 00:24:49.063
I think little Dani Burnier's
leg might be made better.

313
00:24:50.649 --> 00:24:52.523
- How could that be?

314
00:24:52.523 --> 00:24:55.450
- There's a doctor at the
hotel where my sister works

315
00:24:55.450 --> 00:24:57.530
who can mend broken bones.

316
00:24:57.530 --> 00:25:00.070
My sister said he'd want a lot of money.

317
00:25:00.070 --> 00:25:01.456
I'm going over the pass now

318
00:25:01.456 --> 00:25:05.030
to ask him to come and
have a look at Dani.

319
00:25:05.030 --> 00:25:08.720
- You're going over the
pass, in this weather?

320
00:25:08.720 --> 00:25:10.023
My boy you must be mad.

321
00:25:11.300 --> 00:25:13.820
You couldn't cross the
pass in this weather.

322
00:25:13.820 --> 00:25:15.960
- I think I could on my skis,

323
00:25:15.960 --> 00:25:19.140
the fresh snow won't be
too deep yet if I hurry.

324
00:25:19.140 --> 00:25:21.590
But it's no good going
unless I've got the money.

325
00:25:24.050 --> 00:25:26.803
- I would give the money
if I was sure of the man,

326
00:25:28.290 --> 00:25:30.033
but what do we know of him?

327
00:25:31.461 --> 00:25:33.590
Suppose he should cheat us.

328
00:25:33.590 --> 00:25:36.410
- My sister said he's a very famous man.

329
00:25:36.410 --> 00:25:39.709
Monsieur Givert I think.

330
00:25:39.709 --> 00:25:41.209
- Monsieur Givert?

331
00:25:42.181 --> 00:25:43.770
Do you know anymore about him?

332
00:25:43.770 --> 00:25:46.230
- He's got a clinic down by the lake

333
00:25:46.230 --> 00:25:48.380
people come to him from
all over the world.

334
00:26:00.940 --> 00:26:03.790
- Take it all and give
it to Monsieur Givert

335
00:26:03.790 --> 00:26:07.150
and tell him it is the payment of a debt.

336
00:26:07.150 --> 00:26:08.840
- Thank you very much.

337
00:26:08.840 --> 00:26:11.067
- Now you won't forget
the message will you?

338
00:26:11.067 --> 00:26:13.990
- No, I'll say it's a payment of a debt.

339
00:26:13.990 --> 00:26:15.610
- And don't tell him about me.

340
00:26:15.610 --> 00:26:16.725
- No?

341
00:26:16.725 --> 00:26:18.250
- Nor my name.

342
00:26:18.250 --> 00:26:19.820
- No, I don't know your name.

343
00:26:19.820 --> 00:26:21.160
- Nor where I live.

344
00:26:21.160 --> 00:26:23.738
- No I'll just say it's
a payment of a debt.

345
00:26:23.738 --> 00:26:24.831
Bye bye.

346
00:26:24.831 --> 00:26:27.914
- Goodbye and be careful, be careful.

347
00:26:33.434 --> 00:26:36.100
(ski's scraping)

348
00:26:36.100 --> 00:26:38.683
(wind howling)
